\[\frac{BX}{|\sin (90^\circ - \alpha)|} = \frac{7}{\sin 45^\circ},\]so $BX = 7 \sqrt{2} |\cos \alpha|.$

Again, depending on the positions of the lines, $XZ$ is the sum or the difference of $BX$ and $BZ,$ which means it is of the form
